      • isPlayerHead

        boolean isPlayerHead()
        Checks whether the skulltype uses a playerhead internally. This indicates that either the skulltype is PLAYER or a mob without a vanilla head item, generally. Note: This does not necessarily indicate the material of the head - On certain server versions, even Player-Head items are variants of Skeleton skulls.
        Returns:
        true: the skulls is implemented using a playerhead. false: the skull has a different associated item

      • isVanilla

      • getImplementationDetails

        SkullDetails getImplementationDetails()
        Get the underlying bukkit implementation details for the head on this server version. Includes things like the material id for blocks, items, skinnability, etc.
        Returns:
        an object providing implementation details
